    <title>Mountain-top repeaters and solar-powered Wi-Fi: Guest Post from Nepal Wireless</title>
    <link>http://commotionwireless.net/fr/node/8726</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot; property=&quot;content:encoded&quot;&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; class=&quot;media-image attr__typeof__foaf:Image img__fid__236 img__view_mode__media_large attr__format__media_large&quot; height=&quot;360&quot; src=&quot;https://commotionwireless.net/sites/commotionwireless.net/files/styles/large/public/IMG_0759.JPG?itok=wKot-CrU&quot; typeof=&quot;foaf:Image&quot; width=&quot;480&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Open Technology Institute convened over a dozen community&amp;nbsp;technologists from across India and Nepal for the first &lt;a href=&quot;https://commotionwireless.net/blog/commotion-travels-india-first-international-workshop&quot;&gt;international&amp;nbsp;Commotion Wireless workshop&lt;/a&gt; in June. Over the next several weeks, we&amp;nbsp;will be highlighting their innovative grassroots community technology&amp;nbsp;projects on our blog. Our first guest post is from&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Mahabir Pun&lt;/strong&gt;, co-founder of&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nepalwireless.net/index.php&quot;&gt;Nepal Wireless Networking Project&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
